  "local_port": 54098,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply for commercial gas connection in Bangalore?",
  "response": "To apply for a commercial gas connection in Bangalore, you will need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Choose a Gas Provider**: The two main providers in Bangalore are Indian Oil Corporation (Indane) and Bharat Petroleum (Bharat Gas). You can choose either based on your preference and proximity to their distributors.\n\n2. **Locate a Distributor**: Visit the official website of the gas provider you choose and find a distributor near your commercial establishment. You can use their dealer locator tool to find the nearest one.\n\n3. **Download and Fill the Application Form**: You can download the application form from the provider's website or collect it directly from the distributor. Fill out the form with all the necessary details.\n\n4. **Gather Required Documents**: You will need to submit the following documents along with your application:\n   - Proof of Identity (Aadhaar card, PAN card, etc.)\n   - Proof of Address (Aadhaar card, utility bill, etc.)\n   - Business Registration Certificate\n   - No Objection Certificate (NOC) from the owner of the premises (if applicable)\n\n5. **Submit the Application**: Submit the filled application form along with the required documents to the distributor. Some distributors might also allow you to submit the application online.\n\n6. **Pay the Security Deposit and Installation Charges**: You will need to pay a security deposit and installation charges. The amount may vary depending on the provider and the type of connection you are applying for.\n\n7. **Installation and Safety Inspection**: Once your application is processed and approved, a technician will visit your premises to install the gas connection. They will also conduct a safety inspection to ensure that the installation meets safety standards.\n\n8. **Receive Your Connection**: After the installation and safety check, you will receive your commercial gas connection. You can then start using the gas for your business.\n\nMake sure to keep all the documents and receipts safe for future reference. If you encounter any issues during the application process, you can contact the customer service of your chosen gas provider for assistance.",
